Neural Networks, Probabilistic Methods. 

Neural Networks: The paper proposes a method for combining the forecasts of multiple neural networks to improve the accuracy of time series forecasting. The authors use a feedforward neural network with a single hidden layer and sigmoid activation function to model the time series data. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper uses a probabilistic approach to combine the forecasts of the neural networks. Specifically, the authors use a Bayesian framework to estimate the posterior distribution of the forecast errors and use this distribution to weight the forecasts of the individual neural networks. The authors also use a wavelet transform to decompose the time series into different frequency bands and apply the neural network forecasts to each band separately.
